# Environment Variables Template

Copy this to `.env` and fill in your values.

## API Configuration

```bash
# Database
DATABASE_URL=postgresql+psycopg2://snipets:snipets@localhost:5432/snipets

# Supabase Authentication
SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project.supabase.co
SUPABASE_JWKS_URL=https://your-project.supabase.co/auth/v1/.well-known/jwks.json

# CORS
FRONTEND_URL=http://localhost:3000

# Auth (for local development - disable auth checks)
DISABLE_AUTH=true
AUTH_BYPASS_USER_ID=test-user
```

## Frontend Configuration

```bash
# API
VITE_API_URL=http://localhost
VITE_API_PORT=8000

# Supabase
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project.supabase.co
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-anon-key
```

## Docker Compose Configuration

```bash
# Ports
API_PORT=8000
WEB_PORT=3000
POSTGRES_PORT=5432
```

## Production

For production deployment, ensure:
- `DISABLE_AUTH=false`
- `SUPABASE_URL` and `SUPABASE_JWKS_URL` are set
- `FRONTEND_URL` matches your domain
- Database URL uses production database
- All environment variables are secured (no Git commits)
